    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Diagnostics Manual - Electronic Control Systems Diagnostics - Circuit Diagnostics - Brake
        Switch Circuits
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s305010706.6" svcproctype="diagnose" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Brake Switch Circuits</title>
        <svcprocinfo id="s305010706.6.1">
            <figure id="f305010731" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/j31073.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"/>
                <caption>Function diagram for brake switch circuits</caption>
            </figure>
            <para id="s305010706.6.1.1"></para>
            <table id="t305010751" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>The functional diagram for the brake switch circuits includes the following:</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Electronic Control Module (ECM)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Brake Pressure Switch (BPS)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Brake ON/OFF (BOO) switch</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Output - cancels cruise control</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Output - cancels Power Takeoff (PTO) control</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Output - cancels Cold Ambient Protection (CAP)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Output - cancels Idle Shutdown Timer (IST)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>
                <title>Function</title>The brake switch circuit signals the ECM when the brakes are applied. The
                information is used to disengage the cruise control and PTO functions. The brake signal will interrupt
                the CAP feature and will reset the time interval for the IST feature.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>CF chassis has a switching delay between the BOO and BPS signals.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="s305010706.6.2">
            <title>Brake Switch Circuit Operation</title>
            <figure id="f305010732" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/j31339.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"/>
                <caption>Brake switch circuit diagram</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <title>Fault Detection/Management</title>The ECM continuously monitors the BOO circuit at Pin X1-15 and
                BPS at Pin X1-16. If the ECM receives a mismatch signal such as an open BPS and an open BOO a DTC will
                be set.
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>Brake Switch Circuits DTCs</title>DTCs are read using the EST or by counting the flashes from the
                amber and red lamps.
            </para>
            <table id="t305010752" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>DTC 222</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Brake switch circuit Fault</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>DTC 222 is set by the ECM when BPS and BOO are mismatched.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>DTC 222 can be set for an open or shorted BOO switch circuit, an open BPS switch
                                    circuit, an open VIGNcircuit, or a failed BOO or BPS switch.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para></para>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s305010706.6.3">
            <title>Brake Switch Circuits Pin-Point Diagnostics</title>
            <figure id="f305010733" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/j31339.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="532px"/>
                <caption>Brake switch circuit diagram</caption>
            </figure>
            <table id="t305010753" tblwidth="pg-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Voltage Checks - Brake Switch Circuits at ECM</title>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.60*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.77*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.65*"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col3" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>Turn ignition switch to OFF. Connect Breakout Box X1 and X3 to ECM and harness.
                                    Turn ignition switch to ON.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Test Point</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Spec</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>X1-15 to X3-7</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Normal state = 0 V</para>
                                <para>Pedal depressed = B+</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If not within specification, check for blown fuse, open circuit, short to ground,
                                    short to power, or failed switch.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>X1-16 to X3-7</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Normal state = B+</para>
                                <para>Pedal depressed = 0 V</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If not within specification, check for blown fuse, open circuit, short to ground,
                                    short to power, or failed switch.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para></para>
            <table id="t305010754" tblwidth="pg-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Harness Resistance Checks - Brake Switch Circuits to Chassis Ground</title>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="2.00in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="3.00*"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col3" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <warning>
                                    <para>To avoid personal injury, death, including damage to the engine or vehicle,
                                        always disconnect main negative battery cable first. Always connect the main
                                        negative battery cable last.
                                    </para>
                                </warning>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <caution>
                                    <para>To avoid engine damage, turn ignition switch to OFF before unplugging relays
                                        or the ECM module. Failure to turn ignition switch to OFF could cause a voltage
                                        spike and damage the electrical components.
                                    </para>
                                </caution>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>Turn ignition switch to OFF. Connect Breakout Box X1 to wiring harness only.
                                    Disconnect negative battery cable, use negative battery cable as ground test point.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Test Point</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Spec</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>X1-15 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>> 1 k&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If less than 1 k&#x2126;, check for short to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>X1-16 to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>> 1 k&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If less than 1 k&#x2126;, check for short to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <table id="t305010755" tblwidth="pg-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Harness Resistance Checks - ECM to Switch</title>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="2.00in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="3.00*"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col3" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <warning>
                                    <para>To avoid personal injury, death, including damage to the engine or vehicle,
                                        always disconnect main negative battery cable first. Always connect the main
                                        negative battery cable last.
                                    </para>
                                </warning>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <caution>
                                    <para>To avoid engine damage, turn ignition switch to OFF before unplugging relays
                                        or the ECM module. Failure to turn ignition switch to OFF could cause a voltage
                                        spike and damage the electrical components.
                                    </para>
                                </caution>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>Turn ignition switch to OFF. Connect Breakout Box X1 to wiring harness only.
                                    Disconnect negative battery cable, use negative battery cable as ground test point.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Test Point</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Spec</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>X1-15 to switch</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60; 5 &#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If greater than 5 &#x2126;, check for open circuit.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>X1-16 to switch</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60; 5 &#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If greater than 5 &#x2126;, check for open circuit.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
